Source: Evening Post
Author:
Vol / Page: 10
Edition:
Quote: A definition as quoted by Susie Moncrief, creator of world of wearable art, is that wearable art is a piece of art work created not to be hung on a wall but to adorn the body. With wearable art the body becomes a hangar for a sculptured work of art this is not a static display but one that moves with the body to capture the characteristics of the creation.
